pe or Windows Runtime type, you cannot use the placement form of operator [ref new, gcnew](../../windows/ref-new-gcnew-cpp-component-extensions.md) or [new](../../cpp/new-operator-cpp.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates C3828 and shows how to fix it:  \n  \n```  \n// C3828a.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr  \nref struct M {  \n};  \n  \nref struct N {  \n   static array<char>^ bytes = gcnew array<char>(256);  \n};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   M ^m1 = new (&N::bytes) M();   // C3828  \n   // The following line fixes the error.  \n   // M ^m1 = gcnew M();  \n}  \n```"}